    <has_dmc>No</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is:

        1. To establish and compare the diagnostic utilities for hepatocellular carcinoma (HCC)
           screening tests of (a) HS-AFP, (b) AFP + US,(c) AFP alone and (d) US alone (within HBV
           carriers between age 40 and 70 years);

        2. To establish the cost-effectiveness of the screening tests;

        3. To compare tumor sizes, resection rates, and survival rates up to 18 months between
           those who were screened by HS-AFP those of a historical control group that was not
           screened.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
